SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 152
By Crowe
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Albert Lee Fatherree II
of Johnson City.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Albert Lee Fatherree II; and
WHEREAS, Albert Fatherree was an exemplary public servant and consummate
professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, born to Albert Lee Fatherree, Sr., and Altie Gates Fatherree in Memphis,
Mr. Fatherree graduated from Memphis State University; and
WHEREAS, having worked part time for Sears during college, Mr. Fatherree completed
a forty-three-year career with the company in credit management, in which position he earned
the respect of his colleagues and clients alike for the exemplary quality of his work; and
WHEREAS, in 1988, Mr. Fatherree was transferred to Johnson City to start up Sears
Payment Systems (SPS), and, under his leadership, the company grew from 150 to 2,500
employees; in 2000, SPS was purchased by Citi Group, and Mr. Fatherree retired; and
WHEREAS, Albert Fatherree also served as a member of the Chamber of Commerce,
becoming president in 1997 and being named to the Chamber's Hall of Fame in 2017; he
served on many boards and committees throughout the years for business and charitable
organizations; and
WHEREAS, a dedicated patriot, Mr. Fatherree served on active duty during the 1962
Cuban Crisis with the U.S. Air Force; and
WHEREAS, Albert Fatherree was an active and devout member of Munsey Church for
thirty-five years; he served on the church's administrative board, council, board of trustees, and
other committees and was a proud member of the Emmaus Reunion Group and the Virgil
Anderson Sunday School Class; recently, he had joined Central Baptist Church; and
