WHEREAS, deeply devoted to his family, Mr. Fatherree always endeavored to remain
true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, Albert Fatherree enjoyed the loving companionship of his wife, Lori Caudell
Fatherree, for thirty years, and he was the proud father of Albert Lee Fatherree III and Kerry
(Robert) Tripp; grandfather of Devin (Allison), Emily Francis (Josh), Andrew Tripp, and Ashley
Tripp; and great-grandfather of Lyla Fatherree, Indie Fatherree, and Beau Fatherree, with baby
Francis Fatherree on the way; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Fatherree is further survived by his sister, Betty (David) Quave and his
daughter-in-law, Patti Fatherree; and
WHEREAS, in addition to his parents, Albert Fatherree II was preceded in death by his
first wife of thirty-one years, Donna Smith Fatherree; and
WHEREAS, Albert Lee Fatherree II leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and
probity in public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all his
chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
remember the bountiful life of this exceptional public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Albert Lee Fatherree II,
reflecting fondly upon his impeccable character and his stalwart commitment to living the
examined life with courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Mr. Fatherree.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
